# Outside Inn Studios — Streaming Methods Reference
**Living Document | Last updated March 2026**

> Two methods documented here: the current VPS method (what's running now) and the Mac Mini method (the upgrade). Read both. The VPS method stays relevant as a fallback even after the Mac Mini is in place.

---

## METHOD 1 — Current: VPS + FFmpeg + OBS (What's Running Now)

### How It Works

Two separate encoders compete for one YouTube stream key. Only one can be active at a time. Switching between them requires manually killing one before starting the other — causing a 30–60 second gap on YouTube each way.

```
Lo-Fi Radio (default):
[DigitalOcean VPS: FFmpeg loops HoldtLoop.mp4] → [Restream] → [YouTube @EIWerner]

Live Stream (when going live):
[Laptop: OBS via NVENC] → [Restream] → [YouTube @EIWerner]
```

### Infrastructure

| Component | Details |
|---|---|
| VPS | DigitalOcean, Ubuntu 24.04, 1GB RAM, 1 vCPU, NYC3 |
| Process manager | tmux (session named "stream") |
| Video encoder | FFmpeg — stream-copy, no re-encoding, minimal CPU |
| Relay | Restream Standard (~$16/mo) → YouTube + Twitch when added |
| Lofi file | HoldtLoop.mp4 — 1h40m, 1920x1080, 6fps, H.264 + AAC, ~1.28GB |
| Local encoder | OBS Studio via NVENC (RTX 5070) on AERO X16 laptop |

### The Lofi File — How HoldtLoop.mp4 Was Built

**Source material:**
- 480 PNG frames (1920x1080, sequential 1.png–480.png) — art by Marwan Hasnaoui
- 1h40m lo-fi music loop (LofiLoop.wav) — composed by Carson Thatcher

**Step 1 — Build 6fps silent video from PNGs:**
```bash
ffmpeg -framerate 6 -i "D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtAnimationPNGs1\%d.png" -c:v libx264 -pix_fmt yuv420p "D:\StreamSourceFiles\holdt_6fps.mp4"
```

**Step 2 — Loop animation to match full music duration (6000 seconds = 1h40m):**
```bash
ffmpeg -stream_loop -1 -i "D:\StreamSourceFiles\holdt_6fps.mp4" -i "D:\StreamSourceFiles\LofiLoop.wav" -map 0:v -map 1:a -c:v libx264 -g 12 -keyint_min 12 -c:a aac -t 6000 "D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4"
```
> ⚠️ `-g 12 -keyint_min 12` = 2-second keyframe interval at 6fps. Required for YouTube "Good" stream health. Omitting this causes "Poor" health. Rebuild with these flags if file is replaced.

**Step 3 — Upload to VPS:**
```bash
scp D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 root@[SERVER_IP]:/root/
```

**File locations:**

| File | Location |
|---|---|
| Source PNGs (480 frames) | `D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtAnimationPNGs1\` |
| Lo-Fi music (original WAV) | `D:\StreamSourceFiles\LofiLoop.wav` |
| Intermediate (6fps silent) | `D:\StreamSourceFiles\holdt_6fps.mp4` |
| Final loop (video + audio) | `D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4` |
| VPS copy | `/root/HoldtLoop.mp4` |

> All local source files stored on SanDisk Extreme 2TB SSD (portable, device-agnostic path).

---

### PowerShell Commands — Full Reference

#### Check if lofi stream is running
```powershell
ssh root@[SERVER_IP]
tmux attach -t stream
# If time= values are scrolling → stream is running
# Close the PowerShell window — safe, stream keeps running
```

#### Restart lofi stream after a drop
```powershell
ssh root@[SERVER_IP]
tmux attach -t stream
# Run the FFmpeg command (see credentials doc for full command with stream key)
# Wait until time= starts scrolling
# Close the PowerShell window — stream keeps running
```

#### Go live from OBS — full procedure

**Step 1: Kill the lofi stream (MUST do first)**
```powershell
ssh root@[SERVER_IP]
tmux attach -t stream
# Press Q to stop FFmpeg
# Close the PowerShell window
```

**Step 2: Go live**
```
Open OBS on laptop → Hit Start Streaming → Live
```

**Step 3: Bring Holdt back after stream ends**
```
Stop stream in OBS
```
```powershell
ssh root@[SERVER_IP]
tmux attach -t stream
# Run the FFmpeg command (see credentials doc)
# Wait until time= starts scrolling
# Close the PowerShell window — Holdt is back
```

> ⚠️ Between killing FFmpeg and starting OBS, and between stopping OBS and restarting FFmpeg, YouTube has no input. Expect 30–60 second blip each way. This is unavoidable under the current architecture.

#### Update the video file on VPS
```powershell
# Step 1: Stop FFmpeg (see Go Live Step 1 above)

# Step 2: Upload new file
scp [local_path]/HoldtLoop.mp4 root@[SERVER_IP]:/root/

# Step 3: Restart FFmpeg (see Bring Holdt Back above)
```

#### tmux reference
```powershell
tmux attach -t stream        # Attach to running session
# Ctrl+B then D              # Formal detach (two separate actions, not held)
# Just close the window      # Always safe — tmux keeps FFmpeg running
```

