### Known Issues (VPS Method)

| Issue | Priority | Fix | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| No auto-restart when Restream drops VPS connection | **High** | Build shell loop wrapper on VPS | Needed |
| Keyframe interval ~41s (YouTube health "Poor") on current file | Medium | Rebuild HoldtLoop.mp4 with `-g 12 -keyint_min 12`, re-upload | Pending |
| Credentials in plain text in docs | Medium | Redact, move to password manager | In progress |
| VPS default root password unchanged | Medium | `passwd` on server | Next SSH session |
| No seamless VPS ↔ OBS handoff | Low | nginx-rtmp traffic controller | Deferred |

### Auto-Restart Fix (High Priority — Needed Before Athens)

Wrap the FFmpeg command in a shell loop on the VPS so it automatically restarts if Restream drops the connection:

```bash
while true; do
  ffmpeg [full FFmpeg command with stream key]
  echo "FFmpeg exited — restarting in 5 seconds..."
  sleep 5
done
```

Run this inside the tmux session instead of the bare FFmpeg command. If FFmpeg crashes or Restream drops, it restarts automatically within 5 seconds without SSH intervention.

---

### VPS Method — Honest Limitations

- **30–60 second blip** every time you go live and every time you end a stream. Viewers see nothing.
- **Manual SSH ritual** required before and after every live session. From anywhere in the world.
- **No OBS scene structure** during the lofi radio — FFmpeg just loops the file, no overlays, no Stream Deck control, no warmup/cooldown scenes.
- **Fragile by design** — if you forget to kill FFmpeg before starting OBS, or forget to restart it after, things break.
- **VPS keeps running costs** — $6/mo DigitalOcean (currently covered by $200 free credit through ~late April 2026).

