## Side-by-Side Comparison

| | VPS Method (Now) | Mac Mini Method (Upgrade) |
|---|---|---|
| Zero-blip switching | ❌ 30–60 sec gap | ✅ Instant |
| Laptop can be off | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |
| SSH ritual to go live | ❌ Required every time | ✅ Gone |
| Full OBS scene control | ❌ No (FFmpeg only for lofi) | ✅ Yes |
| Stream Deck control | ⚠️ Live scenes only | ✅ Everything including lofi |
| HTML browser source overlays | ⚠️ Live scenes only | ✅ All scenes |
| Auto-restart if connection drops | ⚠️ Needs shell loop fix | ✅ OBS + Scheduled Stream handles it |
| Works from any location | ✅ VPS is cloud-based | ⚠️ LAN only (home base required) |
| One-time cost | $0 | $499–$530 |
| Monthly cost | $22/mo (VPS + Restream) | $16/mo (Restream only) |
| Setup time | Already done | 3–5 hours + 24hr burn-in |

